# Velxo P2P Overhaul — Instructions for all agents/subagents

## Hard rules (MUST follow)
1. NEVER create new `.md` files. Only edit `UPGRADE_PROGRESS.md` (the single progress tracker).
2. NEVER lose data. Migrations are ADDITIVE ONLY — no column drops, no `prisma migrate reset`, no destructive schema changes. The DB is production. Do not run `prisma migrate reset` or `prisma db push --force-reset`.
3. NEVER build or run locally in a way that could affect the live DB. Do not run `prisma migrate deploy` / `db push` / `generate` against production. Schema edits are additive and committed with code; deployment handles migration.
4. Keep changes minimal, surgical, and consistent with existing code conventions (NestJS backend, Next.js App Router frontend, Tailwind with brand tokens).
5. Do NOT touch the migration SQL files in `backend/prisma/migrations/` unless adding a NEW additive migration folder. Never edit existing migration files.
6. Do NOT modify `UPGRADE_PROGRESS.md` Status Key checkboxes incorrectly — only mark `[x]` when the code is verified complete.
7. After finishing, report exactly which files changed and whether the tracked item is verified.

## Backend conventions
- Service methods live in `backend/src/modules/<module>/<module>.service.ts`, controllers in `*.controller.ts`.
- Responses wrapped with `ApiResponseDto.ok(data, msg)`.
- Use `this.prisma` (PrismaService). Decimal math uses `Decimal` from `@prisma/client/runtime/library`.
- New endpoints must be guarded with `SupabaseJwtGuard` or `JwtAuthGuard` where auth is required.
- Seller level fields: `sellers.sellerLevel` (enum), `avgResponseTimeHours`, `deliverySuccessRate` already exist in schema.

## Frontend conventions
- Components are `'use client'` unless server. Pages under `frontend/src/app/**`.
- API via `api.get/post/patch/delete` from `@/lib/api` OR raw `fetch(${API_BASE}/...)` where used.
- `API_BASE = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:3001/api/v1'`.
- Tailwind uses brand color tokens + `SellerLevelBadge` from `@/components/SellerLevelBadge`.
- Money formatting via `useCurrency().fmt`.
